<h2>What is Plex.tv/link?</h2>
<p>
    <strong>Plex.tv/link</strong> is an official device authorization portal provided by Plex.
    It allows users to connect their Plex account to devices that do not support traditional
    login methods, such as Smart TVs and streaming sticks. Instead of entering an email address
    and password using a remote control, users simply enter a temporary activation code on
    plex.tv/link using a phone or computer.
</p>
<p>
    This method improves usability, enhances security, and ensures that only authorized devices
    gain access to your Plex account and personal media library.
</p>

<h2>Why Plex Uses an Activation Code System</h2>
<p>
    Many television interfaces are not designed for complex text input. Plex solves this problem
    by using a short, time-limited activation code that securely pairs your device with your account.
    This system prevents password exposure and reduces login errors.
</p>

<div class="grid">
    <div class="box">✔ Faster sign-in without typing passwords</div>
