<h2>Security and Privacy Information</h2>
<p>
    Plex.tv/link uses encrypted connections and time-based authorization codes.
    Each code expires after a short period, ensuring unauthorized users cannot access your account.
    Devices can also be removed anytime from your Plex account settings.
</p>

<h2>Plex.tv/link Not Working? Troubleshooting Guide</h2>
<div class="info">
<ul>
    <li>Check that your device and browser are connected to the internet</li>
    <li>Ensure the activation code has not expired</li>
    <li>Restart the Plex app to generate a new code</li>
    <li>Log out and log back into your Plex account</li>
    <li>Clear browser cookies or use an incognito window</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Is Plex.tv/link free to use?</h3>
<p>
    Yes, Plex.tv/link is completely free. However, some Plex features require a Plex Pass subscription.
</p>

<h3>How long is the activation code valid?</h3>
<p>
    Activation codes usually expire within a few minutes for security reasons.
</p>

<h3>Can I activate multiple devices?</h3>
<p>
    Yes, you can activate multiple devices using the same Plex account.
</p>

<h3>Do I need to activate Plex every time?</h3>
<p>
    No, activation is required only once per device unless you log out or reset the app.
</p>

